web_snippets: After winning a gold medal in the 400-meter race at the 1936 Summer Olympics, Archie Williams became an Air Force lieutenant colonel and later a teacher.
Mr. Archie Williams has over 25 years of experience in leadership, acquisition, and program management. He is a highly skilled program manager.
